sub_title: Program Manager @ Adyen | Trainer and Learning Designer
summary:
As a Program Manager of the OPS Academy at Adyen, I am responsible for creating and implementing training solutions that enable our global support teams to provide excellent service to our customers. With over two years of experience in learning design and delivery, I collaborate with various stakeholders to align the training objectives with the business goals and values of Adyen, a leading global payment platform.

I hold a master's degree in Educational Psychology - Human Learning and Performance from Erasmus University Rotterdam, and a bachelor's degree in Psychology, Education and Digital Media from University College Maastricht. My core competencies include interpersonal, organization, and teamwork skills, as well as domain expertise in educational psychology, human learning and performance, and digital media. I am passionate about creating impactful and engaging learning experiences that empower people to grow and succeed in their roles and careers. I bring diverse perspectives and experiences to the team, as I speak four languages [German, French, Italian, and English] fluently and have lived and worked in different countries and cultures. I am always eager to learn new things and challenge myself, and I enjoy working with others who share the same vision and passion.
